"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-08-08-paris-2024-olympics-brume-fails-to-win-medal-in-womens-long-jump\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Ese Brume has failed to win a medal in the women's long jump event at the 2024 Olympic Games.  Ese finished 5th in the final of the event with a mark of 6.70m.  The 28-year-old was expected to win a medal in the women's long jump after claiming bronze three years ago in Tokyo.  Ruth Usoro and Prestina Ochonogor, the two other Nigerians in the final, also failed to make it to the podium.  It was the first time Nigeria would field three athletes in the final of an individual event at the Olympics\\u202f.  Nigeria is yet to win a medal at the ongoing Paris 2024 Olympic Games.  Paris Olympics 2024: Bostwana's Tebogo wins gold medal in 200m final  Transfer: They are buying potential - Terry Gibson on incoming Chelsea target  Paris 2024 Olympics: Nigeria's dismal performance worries enthusiasts  Paris 2024 Olympics: D'Tigress' Wakama wins Best Coach award  Paris 2024 Olympics: Brume vows to  bounce back from disappointing outing  Paris 2024 Olympics: Sports Minister apologises to Nigerians after disastrous outing  Paris 2024 Olympics: Team Nigeria officially finishes without single medal  Paris 2024 Olympics: Nigeria's last medal hope Reuben crashes out in Wrestling  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"